Section.Description: Isotopte Atom Count is the number of isotopes that are not most abundant for the corresponding chemical elements. StringWithMarkup.String: Anhydrous disodium hydrogen phosphate is a white, hygroscopic, odourless powder. Hydrated forms available include the dihydrate: a white crystalline, odourless solid; the heptahydrate: white, odourless, efflorescent crystals or granular powder; and the dodecahydrate: white, efflorescent, odourless powder or crystals
